[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]What role can DFID play in strengthening the health system?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To support the Ministry of Health to develop a longer term vision for the health system 
[normal]–
[normal] and
[normal] to develop
[normal] innovative 
[normal]mechanisms
[normal] 
[normal]and partnerships 
[normal]to finance it. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To encourage
[normal] the government to work in partnership with providers such as MSI to fill gaps, scale up services and harness potential of private providers. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]To encourage the 
[normal]government to train and build the capacity of rural health workers particularly midwives, and to empower them to provide services in isolated rural areas. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]What should DFID be doing more of?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Continue to prioritise investment in health - prioritising sexual and reproductive health services which offer the most cost effective way to improve health and development indicators. 
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Prioritise delivery and access to primary health care services in rural areas and for excluded communities.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Continuing to work with other donors to ensure co-ordination and pooling of resources.
[normal]
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Provision of technical assistance - particularly on health financing, infrastructure investments (
[normal]eg
[normal] for supplies and commodities) and training health workers at scale.
